Date: 0/0/1984
Source: Dictionary of Slang
Author: PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page: 280
Edition:
Quote: <i>curly</i> ... Difficult, as in `That's a curly one' ...(?mostly) Aus.: since ca. 11950. ...2. But in NZ as , e.g., `That was extra curly' (Slatter), it seems to mean `excellent' or `attractive' and to date since ca. 1935.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 33
Edition:
Quote: <i>curly</i> a difficult situation, derived possibly from googly ball in cricket; eg `That second question on the exam paper's a curly one.' Mostly ANZ since 1950.
Notes:
